Heathcote 2006_1

Experiment summary

Some information on the models

Model Original: q_2 = q_5, & r_2 = r_5 (all but highest confidence response mapping of uncertainty and detection states equated)
Q restricted: q_2 = q_5 (all but highest confidence response mapping of uncertainty states equated)
R restricted: r_2 = r_5 (all but highest confidence response mapping of detection states equated)

Some information on convergence

For Model Original

One approach failed: partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Frequentist approach with no pooling (asymptotic.no.MPTinR) had 0.682 as proportion of participants with non-identified parameters. Frequentist approach with complete pooling (asymptotic.complete.MPTinR) had no convergence problems.

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) and with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) both converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait.partial.Treebugs and trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.

For Q restricted

One approach failed: partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Frequentist approach with no pooling (asymptotic.no.MPTinR) had 0.909 as proportion of participants with non-identified parameters. Frequentist approach with complete pooling (asymptotic.complete.MPTinR) had some convergence problems:
rank.fischer = 4, n.parameters = 10, convergence = 0.

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) and with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) both converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait.partial.Treebugs and trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.

For R restricted

One approach failed: partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Frequentist approach with no pooling (asymptotic.no.MPTinR) had 0.591 as proportion of participants with non-identified parameters. Frequentist approach with complete pooling (asymptotic.complete.MPTinR) had no convergence problems.

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) and with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) both converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait.partial.Treebugs and trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
